table-1206-246.pgTitle: Origins of names of places in Etosha National Park
table-1206-246.caption: References
data: A bore-hole in the Karos Conservation Area
Means "place of the bird" after large congregations of birds at the waterhole.
For the road running parallel (and a few kilometers north) to "the 19S latitude" eastwards from Duineveld towards Ozonjuitji m'bari.
Means "thirst land" for the bore-hole that was drilled in the dry area to attract wildlife.
Means "place of adversity" and the place was called so because of the hardships faced in the drilling of this borehole.
It is named for a bore-hole that existed on a well-used elephant migration path.
Named for a bore-hole that had bitter taste because of high magnesia content in the water
Named for a "devilish fire" that ravaged the area in the 1960s.
Means "without head" for a windmill that kept losing its head wheel due to strong winds.
Named after a bore-hole was drilled in the area with skepticism of it being successful to attract wildlife.
"Omuramba" means "flooded water course", but meaning of Onaiso is not known. It is the name of an east-west depression that runs for about kilometres (mi).
A bore-hole at the southernmost point of a cone-shaped pan.
A pan named after Pan Point, which incidentally got its name from the pan.
From a bore-hole that existed here that produced very alkaline water
Literally means "to grab something away from a person" but its origin is unknown.
Bore-hole that got its name from its sponsors Ada and Max Kessler. The watering hole has since been closed.
The third largest pan in the park and was named after the Adamax bore-hole located on the edge of the pan.
Refers to the bitter taste of water in the area
Means "the river that comes from far away"

One interpretation means "place nearby the point (of the peninsula)". Another interpretation means "big locusts" or "there not big locusts" depending on a slight variation in the pronunciation, referring to the "eyes" formed in the depression.
Implies "fine stone grit" and is known by other names Karagas, //Haraxas, Kora or Thiachab.
Also called !Gomses and means "soil deep in the hole is always wet"
Means "red soil" for the soil in the area.
Originally called Geikoitsaub and means "large waterhole"
Means "place where sun is so hot you cannot even sit in the shade of trees", and is also known as SoreǂAxab.
Probably refers to the sound made by sneezing and is the name of a waterhole.
Means "place from which the waterhole(Tsinaib) can be seen"

Means "ridge that is near to and smaller than Gamgoas"
Means "eland detour hills" and refers to the T-junction made by Rhino Drive, Eland Drive and the road to Halali.
From the noise that water makes when moving over rocks
Means "rhino food" and refers to the spring west of the Etosha lookout. It could probably refer to the plants that rhinos eat or for the a rhino that was killed there.
Means "very salty water" and refers to the seepage close to the Etosha Lookout road. It is also called /Oses or /Huruses.

It means "you always turn back to the water which is pleasant tasting" and alternatively means "I was not at this place when the event or argument you speak off took place"
It was a popular spot for poachers because it was a good vantage point to hunt game as well as spot approaching conservators well in advance
Literally means "the water becomes less" but is sometimes referred to as "waterhole of the snakes" because of frequent encounters with the reptiles in the vicinity
Chudop means "black mud". Its original name was probably Aub (the name for another waterhole)
Means "fountain". Its original name was probably "/Ciob" meaning "many stones in the water" and Aub was probably the name for Chudop.
Means "lion drink" probably referring to the waterhole where lions frequently came for a drink
Means "lion's den" or "lion's haunt", from frequent encounters with lions in the area

data: Two homes suffered significant roof damage. A garage was destroyed, causing part of the roof to be removed from the attached home. 33 homes in all were damaged and several trees were downed.
44 homes were either damaged or destroyed, with structural damage reported to several homes. Several trees were downed as well. Three people were injured.

Brief tornado destroyed a house that was under construction.
Many trees and power lines were downed and the roof was removed from a home.
Weak tornado downed a few trees.
A large, newly constructed shed was destroyed, a house lost its roof, and numerous pine trees were downed.
Long track tornado that was up to yards (m) wide. Three outbuildings were destroyed, with another severely damaged. Two homes suffered minor damage and numerous trees were uprooted.
Very brief tornado that was up to yards (m) wide. The skirting of a mobile home was damaged and numerous trees were uprooted.

A few buildings were damaged and trees were downed.

title: Week 1
Entrances

Mikkayla, Xavier, Tahan, Tully, Matthew and Caleb entered the Halfway House on Day 0. Ben, Tim, Sharon, Ed, Heidi and Jasmin entered the Safe House on Day 0. Drew and Jade entered the Safe House on Day 1.
table-1206-921.caption: Weekly Summary
data: On Day 0, Tahan decided to cross the divide between the two houses; as a result, she had to return all of her clothes to Big Brother, where they were kept for 24 hours. As Caleb got half way across the divide, he had to return half of his clothes to Big Brother, where they were also kept for 24 hours. When their suitcases were returned, however, they were empty. On Day 3, their clothes were finally returned to them after Heidi succeeded in her secret task (see Tasks).

On Day 0, before the housemates entered the house, they had to choose one of twelve keys which would decide where they would live. Half of the keys led to the Safe House; the other half led to the Halfway House. The housemates living in the Safe House were treated to luxurious accommodation and privileges, whilst those living in the Halfway House were not. On Day 1, new housemates Drew and Jade found out that they would have to pretend to be a married couple for the first week of the season. If they fooled their fellow housemates for a week then they would be immune from the first eviction, but if they were unsuccessful they would both automatically face eviction.
Rohan and Katie & Lucy entered the Safe House on Day 8.
On Day 9, as punishment for passing food over the divide, Tahan had to paint an entire bucket of black coal white.

On Day 9, housemates began their second weekly shopping task; 'An Ashes Test'. For this task, the garden was transformed into a cricket pitch. When instructed to do so by Big Brother, one-by-one each Safe House housemate took turns to bat for their house and protect their stumps against an automatic cricket ball bowling machine. The Halfway House housemates were required to keep a fire burning in the garden throughout. On the night of Day 9, Xavier and Tully had to become watchmen and sleep outside on the cricket pitch to watch the night through a telescope. By Day 10, housemates only lost 19 of a maximum 20 wickets, and therefore passed the task. On Day 9, Ben had to impress Big Brother in an interview to become Big Brother's personal assistant. He passed this task. On Day 10, it was Ben's first day as Big Brother's PA. On Day 10, Tahan and Rohan were given a Diary Room challenge to win luxury ingredients for the weekly family dinner. They had to answer a series of questions whilst sitting in an ice cold bath. Tahan passed the task, despite Rohan getting out of the bath within seconds of entering it. While all the housemates received a luxury family dinner later that night, Rohan was given canned chicken. On Day 12, housemates took part in their second Showdown. Ed was the winner and was rewarded with $5,000, the nominations superpower, and a night in the Presidential Suite with Sharon, the housemate of his choice. On Day 15, after the eviction, each contestant had to individually predict the future of their fellow housemates.

On Day 7, Drew and Jade's secret task was revealed to the other housemates. However, they failed the task as everyone except Ben and Matthew did not believe they were a real married couple. Drew and Jade were therefore automatically nominated for eviction. On Day 8, as Katie & Lucy are competing as a single housemate, Big Brother told them that they have to stay within three metres of each other throughout their stay in the house. On Day 9, after the nomination results had been announced, the nominated housemates were sent to the Halfway House. On Day 10, Tahan volunteered to answer a question by Big Brother unaware that he wanted her to save a nominated housemate from eviction and replace them with someone else. She chose to swap Mikkayla with Heidi, meaning the pair swapped sides and Mikkayla no longer faced eviction.

On Day 7, Drew and Jade were nominated automatically to face eviction (see Twists). On Day 9, the housemates nominated for the first time. Mikkayla, Sharon, Jasmin, and Tim received the most nomination points and therefore joined Drew and Jade as the housemates nominated for eviction during this week. The nominated housemates had to move directly to the Halfway House later that day. On Day 10, Heidi was nominated for eviction following Tahan's decision to replace Mikkayla with her as the new nominee (see Twists).
On Day 15, Sharon became the first housemate to be evicted from the Big Brother House.

On Day 17, a pet dog known as 'Mr Clooney' entered the Big Brother House and Mikkayla became his Chief Carer. 'Mr Clooney' was allowed access to all areas of the Big Brother House, including the Safe and Halfway Houses. He was able to go between houses via a Doggy Door located in the yard on the fence dividing the two houses.

On Day 16, housemates undertook their third weekly shopping task; 'Big Brothers Ice Cream Shop'. To pass the task housemates had to deliver accurate ice cream orders to Big Brother within the time allocated only from memory. Housemates were not allowed to write down any orders. On Day 17, housemates failed the shopping task, having incurred six of a possible five fails. On Day 17, Katie & Lucy were given a Diary Room Challenge in which they had to play a game of charades and get at least half or more of the answers correct to win a series of luxury items. However, if they failed they would receive only basic items. Katie & Lucy later passed the task. On Day 19, housemates took part in their third weekly Showdown. Tully was the winner and was rewarded with $5,000, the nominations superpower, and a night in the Presidential Suite with Tahan, the housemate of her choice.

On Day 16, housemates nominated. Ben, Mikkayla, Rohan, Tahan, Tully and Xavier received the most nomination points and faced eviction this week. On Day 17, after Mikkayla chose to save herself and replace herself with Matthew, Matthew was nominated for eviction (see Twists).

On Day 22, a double eviction took place. Rohan became the second housemate to be evicted from the Big Brother House. Shortly after, Xavier became the third housemate to be evicted from the Big Brother House.

On Day 23, housemates began their fourth weekly shopping task; 'The Yes/No Challenge.' In this challenge, housemates had to say yes to all tasks Big Brother asked them to do. If they succeeded in their respective challenges they earned a certain number of pass or fail balls to put into a lottery, which was drawn at the end of the task. This would determine whether the housemates had passed the task or not. On Day 25, the lottery was drawn and the housemates passed the task. On Day 24, Drew and Tim participated in the game 'Our Little Secret' to try to obtain luxury food items for a seafood platter for the weekly family dinner. To keep the food they had to resist as many items as possible, and for every item that they could not resist one item of the seafood platter treat would not be achievable. At the end of this task, the seafood platter was handed to the housemates, with or without some or all of its original ingredients. On Day 24, housemates participated in the fourth weekly Showdown, of which Jade was the winner. As a reward for winning, Jade earned the save and replace ability (see Nominations) and a night in the Presidential Suite with Katie & Lucy, the housemate of her choice.

On Day 23, after the nomination results had been announced, the nominated housemates were sent to the Halfway House. On Day 24, the Halfway House and Safe House housemates joined together to make one house, with the divides removed between them and all housemates then moving to the Safe House. A new bedroom was also unveiled. http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2013/08/nine-adds-late-night-big-brother.html On Day 30, the fourth evicted housemate, Jasmin, was allowed to give the Nominations Super Power to the housemate of her choice; she chose to give it to Heidi. http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2013/08/nine-adds-late-night-big-brother.html

On Day 23, housemates nominated. Jade, Jasmin, Katie & Lucy, Matthew, Mikkayla and Tahan received the most nomination points and faced eviction this week. On Day 24, after winning Showdown this week, Jade was rewarded with the 'save and replace' ability. She later chose to save herself and nominate Ben in her place.
On Day 29, Jasmin became the fourth housemate to be evicted from the Big Brother House.

On Day 30, housemates nominated. Caleb, Ed, Jade, Mikkayla, Tahan and Tully received the most nomination points and faced eviction this week. On Day 31, after winning Showdown this week, Tim was rewarded with the 'save and replace' ability. He later chose to save Mikkayla and nominate himself in her place.
On Day 36, Caleb became the fifth housemate to be evicted from the Big Brother House.

On Day 37, housemates began their next weekly shopping task 'Battle of the Bands', in this task housemates were split into two teams of boys and girls, the boys became known as ManDate and the girls became known as HotPantz. Housemates then had to learn and perform a song chosen by Big Brother which would then be placed on the internet for viewers to watch to pass the task housemates had to have more than 50,000 people watch their videos. On Day 39, housemates passed the task as more than 50,000 people watched their clips, passing this weeks shopping task. On Day 43, the band/group with the highest views will perform live on the eviction show, HotPantz received more views/likes then ManDate and performed on the 5th eviction night.

On Day 37, housemates nominated. Drew, Heidi, Mikkayla, Tahan, Tim, Tully received the most nomination points and faced eviction this week. On Day 38, after winning Showdown this week, Mikkayla was rewarded with the 'save and replace' ability. She later chose to save herself and nominate Ben in her place.
On Day 43, Heidi became the sixth housemate to be evicted from the Big Brother House.

On Day 44, housemates commenced their 7th weekly shopping task, the task was 'Time is Money'. In this task an hourglass and a cash-booth (containing $500) were placed in the laundry area of the backyard. Throughout the task housemates will complete in time based challenges to win buckets of sand/time to win for the hourglass, if housemates fail challenges they will lose sand/time. At the end of the task one housemate will enter the cash-booth, this housemate must collect as much money as possible before the sands of time run out. On Day 46, Tully was chosen by Big Brother to enter the cash-booth to try and collect as much money as possible, housemates collected 1:18 minutes for Tully to complete the task. Tully successfully collect $430 of the available $500. On Day 45, Ed and Matthew were called to diary room to take part in the task 'Dance for your Dinner', they were playing for Gourmet food items or basic food items for the nights family dinner. When the game starts housemates need to put on a set of headphones and then dance non-stop for half an hour. Housemates passed this task thus gaining the luxury food items for family dinner.

On Day 43, It was revealed that on Day 50 a double eviction will occur, however this will be a fake double eviction, with the housemate receiving the least number of votes to save being evicted and the housemate with the highest number of votes to save being 'fake' evicted and move next door to the Presidential Suite. On Day 50, Ben was "Fake" Evicted and was moved to the Presidential Suite were he would stay until re-entering the Big Brother 24 hours later.

On Day 44, housemates nominated. Ben, Ed, Jade, Katie & Lucy, Mikkayla, Tahan. Ed received the most nomination points. On Day 45, after winning Showdown, Drew was given the 'save and replace ability'. He chose to save Jade from eviction and replace her with Matthew
On Day 50, Matthew became the seventh housemate to be evicted from the Big Brother House.

As of Week 8 only 4 nominees will be placed up for eviction and instead of the winner of Showdown receiving the 'Save and Replace Ability' they would only have the 'Safe Ability' which means that only three housemates will face the public vote.

On Day 51, Mikkayla was given her first strike, after she accidentally revealed a comment about nominations to Katie & Lucy. On Day 53, Katie & Lucy were punished for being more than 3 metres apart from each other, and their punishment was to hold hands with each other until further notice.

On Day 51, Jade, Katie & Lucy, Tahan, Tully. Received the most nominations and were therefore put up for eviction. On Day 52, after winning Showdown, Tim won the Save Ability and chose to save Jade from the week's nominations. Katie & Lucy, Tahan and Tully were still up for eviction.
On Day 57, Tully became the eighth housemate to be evicted from the Big Brother House.

On Day 57, Bert and Patti Newton entered the house as a special birthday surprise for Ben, they stayed for a short time before leaving. On Day 58, it was revealed that two new male housemates would enter the Big Brother house, Justynn and Nathan On Day 61, it was revealed that two new female housemates would enter the Big Brother, Madaline and Boog.

On Day 58, housemates began their 9th weekly shopping task, the LOL task. To pass the task, housemates were required to laugh out loud whenever they heard the LOL sound effect and must continue to laugh uncontrollably until they heard the LOL sound effect again. If housemates did not laugh uncontrollably at a sound effect, housemates would fail the task. On Day 60, housemates passed their weekly shopping task; they received a luxury shopping budget for doing so. On Day 59, Tim and Justynn were called the diary room to determine whether or not they would receive gourmet (Asian feast) or basic (prawn crackers) food items for the evening family dinner. The name of the task was Mind Reader: Big Brother asked a series of questions and Justynn was required to write down Tim's answers to the questions by 'reading his mind' to receive the gourmet food items Justynn was required to complete 4 of the 7 questions correctly. They failed the tasked and only received the basic food items for the family dinner. On Day 63, housemate began their tenth weekly shopping task, 'Ranking Order'. Housemates had to rank themselves in order of various questions asked by Big Brother; whilst this was occurring, one housemate could see the housemates ranking with no sound they had to guess from a few suggestions what the housemates were ranking. In the end, housemates passed the weekly shopping task thus gaining a luxury shopping budget. On Day 64, Boog and Mikkalya were called to the diary room to take part in a family dessert challenge for a late-night dessert of chocolate fondue or a single m&m each. The task was called 'Brain Invaders'; in this task Mikkayla had to read Boog's mind and answer the questions just has Boog had answered them. Housemates passed this task and gained chocolate fondue for the whole house.
On Day 58, it was revealed that one intruder would be evicted from the Big Brother house; to stay within the house, the housemate had to receive the most votes to stay in a jump poll.

On Day 57, it was revealed that there would be no nominations taking place this week. Instead, all the housemates except the two new arrivals would face eviction. On Day 59, after winning Showdown, Tahan chose to save both herself and Ben, starting the voting lines.
On Day 64, Justynn became the ninth housemate to be evicted from the Big Brother House. On Day 66, Katie and Lucy became the tenth housemate to be evicted from the Big Brother House.

On Day 69, housemates began their eleventh weekly shopping task, 'Rock, Paper, Scissors'. To pass the task, housemates were divided into the separate teams; to pass the task, no two teams can occupy the same area of the Big Brother house. If they do enter the same area of the house the rules of rock, paper, scissor come into play; e.g. if scissors are in the kitchen and rock comes in scissor must leave the kitchen area immediately. On Day 72, Big Brother revealed to housemates that they had failed this weeks shopping task for breaking the rules in which complied with it, they received staples to live of for the next week. On Day 71, housemates Ben and Madaline were called to the diary room for this week's family dinner game 'Animal Instinct', they were playing for wither a Mega BBQ or nothing. Madaline was blindfolded while Ben put on different animal outfits and it was up to Madaline to guess what animal Ben was by asking Yes/No questions. Housemates passed the task gaining a Mega BBQ.
On Day 67, nominations took place Ben, Drew, Ed, Tahan, Tim received the most nominations and being placed up for eviction. This week there was no save ability and the voting lines opened.

On Day 70, Nathan voluntarily left the Big Brother house, giving his housemate status to Madaline who had lost the intruder poll. On Day 73, Ben became the eleventh housemate to be evicted from the Big Brother House.

On Day 76, housemates began their twelfth weekly shopping task, 'Double B FM', a radio show in which housemates had to run their own radio station in which a wide range of shows in which they must keep the entertainment going at all times, for if there is any dead air then they would fail the task. On Day 79, housemates were told by Kyle and Jackie'O that they had failed this week's shopping task and would only be receiving a basic shopping budget for the next week. On Day 78, housemates took part in a special Family Dinner Challenge; their prize was either a Gourmet Dinner (lamb, chips, and ice cream) or Budget Meal (Cup-of-Soup), the name of the task was The Family Dinner Auction and they had to bid for the food using there personal possessions they must give up all the items in which Big Brother asks for in order for them to gain there gourmet food. In the end housemates gave all the possessions asked for by Big Brother and they passed and gained a Gourmet Dinner.
On Day 74, nominations took place and Boog, Mikkayla and Tahan were nominated for eviction after receiving the most points. This week there was no save ability and the voting lines opened.
On day 80, Mikkayla became the twelfth housemate to be evicted from the Big Brother House.
On Day 85, ex-housemate Tully returned to the house to participate in the 'Freeze Task', she left a short while after entering.

On Day 82, Big Brother introduced Housemate of the Week; this special privilege entitled the housemate who gains the title solidarity access to the luxury fridge, hot water when ever asked for and access to the parlour when ever asked. For the first housemate of the week, housemates had to plead their case to Big Brother as to why they should gain this title. The Housemate of the Week for this week was Drew. On Day 83, housemates began their thirteenth weekly shopping task, 'Freeze and Release'. In this task, housemates had to freeze in the position they were in at that current time, and are not allowed to move no matter what happens until Big Brother says release. If any one housemate moves when meant to be frozen they will automatically fail the task and they may even receive nominations against there name. On Day 86, housemates passed this weeks shopping task thus gaining a luxury shopping budget. On Day 85, Tim and Madaline were called to the diary room to participate in this week's family dinner challenge 'Kiss the Bride' they were playing for a Gourmet Meal (Burger, Chips, Beer) or Basic Meal (mini versions of the gourmet meal). To gain the Gourmet food items they had to endure three rounds of kissing, the first round was housemates had to pass hovering balls into a box just using there lips, for the second round Tim had to exchange his vows and every time he completed them Madaline had to kiss different types of aquatic life a fish, crab and octopus, for the final round they had to partake in endurance kissing using only there lips they had to hold a heart until they heard the wolf whistle. Housemates passed the task as they completed all three rounds thus gaining a Gourmet Meal for the family dinner, as well as this Tim and Madaline received one night in the Presidential Suite.
On Day 81, nominations took place and Boog, Jade and Madaline received the most nominations and were put of for eviction, as there is no more save ability the voting lines opened.
On Day 87 Madaline became the thirteenth housemate to be evicted.
On Day 88, nominations took place and Drew, Ed, Jade and Tim received the most nomination points and as there was no more save and replace ability the voting lines opened.
On Day 94, Ed became the fourteenth housemate to be evicted
On day 99, in a double eviction Boogs and Drew were the fifteenth and sixteenth housemates to be evicted, leaving Tim, Tahan and Jade in the grand finale.

data: An aggressively hopped ale brewed to a style pioneered in the Pacific Northwest known as Cascadian IPA or Black IPA. Essentially an India Pale Ale with additional crystal malt and roasted malts for layered flavors with very little roast character relative to its dark color.

This traditional Oktoberfest beer is brewed to be enjoyed throughout the fall. Big malty biscuit flavors are balanced by an alcohol warmth and a dry finish. Crisp hop bitterness and noble hop aroma round out this seasonal lager.
A Double IPA brewed with 30% rye, large quantities of American hops, and fermented with Belgian ale yeast to create a bitter, hoppy, and spicy ale.

An uncommon Double India Pale Ale which puts a California twist on English brewing traditions by adding an assertive hop aroma and bitterness that compliments the firm malt backbone. Like its little brother Racer 5, Racer X™ is balance in a bottle.
True to the Norgrove's Scottish Heritage, this Wee Heavy is brewed with Scottish malts and lightly hopped with East Kent Goldings. Big and Malty sweet, this ale will have you hearing bagpipes.

data: 40 to 50 homes sustained varying degrees of roof damage. One home had a collapsed wall. One person was injured.
Several homes roof damage in Louisiana. In Arkansas, five structures received heavy damage, four of which were chicken houses. Many trees were downed along the path.
Brief touchdown in an open field resulted in no damage.
Six structures sustained heavy damage, including two mobile homes. Several other structures suffered minor damage and many trees were downed. Five people were injured.

A house suffered major damage and a mobile home was destroyed. Three more houses sustained minor damage and several sheds and outbuildings were destroyed. Thousands of trees were downed, as were many power poles. Six people were injured.

Many trees were downed, some of which landed on a vehcle and a mobile home. Windows were blown out of a house, a metal barn was damaged, and a large metal shop building was destroyed. Part of a house was destroyed and several other shop buildings sustained damage. Many trees were downed.
A grain storage facility, a few homes, several metal shop buildings, and several trailers/mobile homes were damaged. Several sheds and outbuildings were destroyed and many trees were downed.
Several trees were downed as the tornado remained over a heavily wooded area.
Two homes, one business, and several farm buildings were damaged. Trees and power lines were downed.
Numerous trees, power poles, and metal signs were downed. Several sheds and a carport were destroyed, a church lost part of its roof, a fence was damaged, and an irrigation pivot was flipped.
One mobile home had its roof blown off, while another suffered minor damage.

table-1206-892.caption: January 5 event
data: Brief tornado downed several trees and power lines. A storage building was damaged, a mobile homes was shifted of its support blocks, and another mobile home suffered roof damage.
The roof of a fire station was damaged, the roof of an old train depot was blown off, and several metal buildings were damaged.
Four chicken houses were destroyed and one house sustained minor damage. Several trees were downed and three additional homes were damage, with one losing its roof.
Numerous trees were snapped and uprooted, two houses suffered roof and wall damage, and seven outbuildings were destroyed.
A brick house had its entire roof removed and a large outbuilding was destroyed. Numerous trees were snapped and uprooted as well.
Many trees and power lines were downed. One house suffered minor roof damage.

Many large trees were downed, some of which fell on homes, and numerous structures were damaged. The damage to the structures included: damage to the roof of a barn, a destroyed greenhouse, minor roof, gutter, and siding damage to at least 30 houses, and several damaged or destroyed outbuildings.
Many large trees were downed, a mobile home was destroyed, and a car was damaged.
Numerous trees were downed and several mobile homes had siding striped off. Another structure was destroyed.

Brief touchdown in the parking lot at an elementary school. Nine vehicles were severely damaged, with four being lifted off of the ground and flipped. A shed was blown over as well. 15 people were injured, most of whom were in cars inside the parking lot.
Two sheds were destroyed and the roof was partially blown off of another shed. Part of the deck was torn away from a house and several pine trees were snapped.
Eight homes sustained minor roof damage and some outbuildings were also damaged.
Source: SPC Storm Reports Reports for 01/04/07, SPC Storm Reports Reports for 01/05/07, NCDC Storm Events Database, NWS Jackson, MS
